<TITLE> All need to be on guard: adviser </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 4 (bdnews24.com)  Commerce adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman has said all need to be on guard so that no subversive acts take place ahead of the general election. Asked to comment on the report that senior Awami League leader Motia Chowdhury had received a letter just as late Gonotontri Party president Nurul Islam did, he said "It's the government's responsibility to maintain a favourable electoral environment. And for that all will have to cooperate with the government." He made the remarks at the launch of a new site on bdnews24.com at Kasturi Restaurant at Gulshan in the city on Thursday. The country's leading online newspaper in partnership with celebrity chef Tommy Miah launched a new site featuring a 'Recipe a Week', designed exclusively for readers to promote the best of Bangladesh around the globe. About bdnews24.com', he said, "It has a good contribution in a brief period since its inception. It has brought new tunes of words in news." "The country has seen a boom of media industry, but bdnews24.com stands out." Foreign adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury, local government adviser Anwarul Iqbal, agriculture adviser CS Karim, chief adviser's press secretary Syed Fahim Munaim, former chief justice Mostafa Kamal, National Museum director general Samsuzzaman Khan, were among those attending the ceremony at the launch at Kasturi Restaurant in Gulshan. bdnews24.c
